amic classes and metadata, which raises some questions. The reachability agent will add reflection entries for specific classes. I should ensure not to compile or run it. I might also need to check the dynamic coverage report and inspect metadata to see if I need to update the user-code-filter.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_eRAzEjECYvFhfVFsoqolPgcM|fc_050a6a7dba0380d80169f48791caa4819e9d7d8820158bad93", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/user-code-filter.json"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/user-code-filter.json\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2757, "output": 1581, "cacheRead": 16384, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20722, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777633149279, "responseId": "resp_050a6a7dba0380d80169f4877e0e08819ea76542307bb342e4"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_eRAzEjECYvFhfVFsoqolPgcM|fc_050a6a7dba0380d80169f48791caa4819e9d7d8820158bad93", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"rules\": [\n    {\n      \"excludeClasses\": \"**\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"includeClasses\": \"freemarker.**\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777633169988}]}
